Сегодня в рубрике #накипело В курьерских службах и разного рода доставках я всегда видела сервис, который, знаете, такой сЭрвис (и при произношении этого слова нужно поправить очки на переносице, поднять указательный палец вверх и, по возможности, добавить "да, сэр"). Sun Wukong also known as the Monkey King, is a mythological figure who features in a body of legends, which can be traced back to the period of the Song dynasty. He appears as a main character in the 16th century Chinese classical novel Journey to the West. He is a monkey born from a stone who acquires supernatural powers through Taoist practices. After rebelling against heaven and being imprisoned under a mountain by the Buddha, he later accompanies the monk Xuanzang on a journey to retrieve Buddhist sutras from "the West". Sun Wukong possesses immense strength; he is able to lift his 13,500 jīn (7,960 kilograms ) staff with ease. He is also extremely fast, able to travel 108,000 li (21,675 kilometres ) in one somersault. (Note that this is more than half way around the world). Sun knows 72 transformations, which allow him to transform into various animals and objects; however, he is troubled in transforming into other forms, due to the accompanying incomplete transformation of his tail. Sun Wukong is a skilled fighter, capable of holding his own against the best warriors of heaven. Each of his hairs possess magical properties, capable of being transformed into clones of the Monkey King himself, and/or into various weapons, animals, and other objects. He knows spells to command wind, part water, conjure protective circles against demons, and freeze humans, demons, and gods alike. One of the most enduring Chinese literary characters, Sun Wukong has a varied background and colorful cultural history. Sun Wukong's origin is from the White Monkey legends from the Chinese Chu kingdom (700–223 BC), who revered gibbons and especially white-colored ones.These legends gave rise to stories and art motifs during the Han dynasty, eventually contributing to the rise of the Sun Wukong figure. Sun Wukong was initially developed as a Taoist immortal before being incorporated into Buddhist myths. He is also considered by some scholars to be influenced by elements of both Chinese folklore and the Hindu deity Hanuman from the Ramayana. . . #throwback #singapore #bencoolen #travelphotography #instagood #instalike #pictoftheday #photooftheday #photography #like4like #nikon

Yaa ga salah sih pemikiran kayak gitu, tapi Allah itu juga Ilmiah. Kalau bener dikabul kayak gitu, pas kita doa nih, ya Allah saya pengen mobil. . Eh tiba2 tuh mobil turun dari langit, gubrak.. Mungkin dikasih lewat sodara, tetangga atau bahkan dari bos kita tuh mobil karena kita silahturahimnya bagus, kerjanya baik dan kagak ketinggalan ibadahnya juga bagus... . Doa mah tetep doa. Ikhtiar juga jalan biar Allah yg kasih jalan yg lebih ilmiah. Mau bisnis ? Tapi kagak daftar, yg gimana mau jalan. Mau komisi ? Tapi kerjannya ngehayal doang ? Ya gimana.. Kuy Gabung dgn Paytren . CreatureS | Savour Comfort On A Plate . . We know that everyday and everthing thing we do is setting the table for you, but while it's our food table, it's your story to tell. Let's face it, no one ever left home to find the ordinary in anything - the same goes for food. We all love to discover something exciting, different and special. But we always always always love to return to the familiar, the comforting and the memorable. . . At CreatureS, our food table is a constant reminder, to not forget self discovery, to express our point of view and to present our art. It is not what we do, it's always about who we are and we will always strive to be your wingman when it comes to putting out comfort food and to seek joy in communal dining on a table filled with love. . . We aim not just to be a trend or a fad. We work towards being an establishment that builds history over time. And the best part about history? It never stops getting written. Step into an atmospheric dining enclave, a milieu designed to eke out bliss, and indulge in simple pleasures in life. . . Last time I was watching Channel News Asia when I saw them featured the Tang Shipwreck cargo that are now displayed in a museum in New York. Suddenly I realized that I was able to see the display personally (for free) last time I visited the Asian Civilisations Museum in Singapore. I was also blessed to unearth some of their collections through the virtual reality experience that the museum offered. Now I'm sharing you some of the photos from my visit.  How significant are these art pieces? The remarkable cargo of more than 60,000 mostly perfectly preserved ceramics discovered from the shipwreck in Java Sea on 1998 has revolutionized the way we see the world in the 9th century.  Upon inspection, it was realised that this was a trade vessel transporting works of art to sell in the Middle East. Until then, historians had had no record of trade routes between the Far East and the Middle East existing in the mid-800s AD.  The discovery also showed that the Chinese artists were making their products more desirable to their Middle Eastern buyers, incorporating styles and motifs that were popular thousands of miles away in Persia. Among the pieces were three dishes with blue and white colouring, which changed our understanding of Chinese ceramics.  The museum curator said that the traditional dating for blue and white is around 14th century but in this shipwreck we saw that they were actually producing blue and white in the 9th century. The blue is from cobalt and cobalt was only available in the Middle East in that period.  The beautiful objects of exceptional rarity testify to the ingenuity of artists and merchants, and show that exotic objects have long been appreciated by the world’s consumers. There’s a certain kind of surprise that comes from realising that these global connections were in existence more than 1,000 years ago because people today think of globalisation as something that is very recent.  #JustMyDay #MyTravelDiary #TangShipwreck #Arts #History #ACM #Museum #Singapore #Discovery #Archeology #Ceramics #Science #FineArts #Blue #Antique #Cargo #Ship #Navigation #맞팔 #싱가포르 #대박 #adventure #CNA

[Petua Penjagaan Cik Bunga Agar Kekal Bersih] . Petua 1 : Bagi wanita yang Cik Bunga selalu berair dan berbau kurang menyenangkan, eloklah mencuba petua ini. Ambil segenggam serbuk teh, letakkan ke dalam mangkuk. Tuangkan air panas, kemudian duduklah di atas mangkuk itu sehingga wapnya terkena faraj anda selama 2 minit. Selepas itu basuh rata-rata dengan air teh itu. Lakukan 2 kali pada waktu pagi dan malam. . Petua 2 : Ambil 2 biji kulit pisang muda, 3 helai daun sireh bertemu urat, sebiji kulit pinang, gambir sebanyak 3 keping dan sedikit kapur sireh. Ramuan tersebut hendaklah ditumbuk sehingga lumat. Kemudian direndamkan dengan setengah baldi air suam panas. Basuhlah faraj anda dengan air tersebut 2 kali sehari pagi dan malam agar ia sentiasa bersih dan segar. . Petua 3 : Untuk mengetatkan Cik Bunga, rebus biji manjakani dan air rebusan itu dijadikan bahan pencuci Cik Bunga. Cik Bunga akan kembali ket.at dan tidak mengeluarkan bau busuk yang amat sangat. . Petua 4: Yup! Ni paling cepat dan semua petua di atas ada lengkap dalam satu botol. Yang ni paling mudah. Guna je Celebrity Feminine Scrub Wash. RM 59.00 CFSW semua dah siap touch n go sahaja. Picture Chinese for the things we see around us! 。 。 💡Do you know that Chinese radicals are like roots in Romance languages?  They give you a clue about a word. 。 。 🌺Today we spot a "hat" - mào zi 帽子 🎩（writing is the same in traditional simplified Chinese). 。 。 ✏️This character has the "towel" -巾- jīn radical.  That indicates this character has something to do with "a piece of cloth, towel, or fabric for head." So this radical gives a clue to the meaning of the character.  The right side of the character is 冒 mào and that is the pronunciation of this character 帽. 。 。 💪Every Chinese character is like a building block.  Some can stand alone and they are individual words.  They then can also combine with other Chinese characters and forming new words. 。 。 🎥 Watch Picture Chinese on YouTube-MissPandaChinese channel and listen to the pronunciation of each word, phrase, and sentence. 👀。 。 。 。 。 。 #misspandachinese #picturechinese #chinese #language #world #china #taiwan #hongkong #Singapore #chinaadoption #heritage #learnchinese #learningchinese #bilingualkids #youtuber #mommybloggers #中文 #漢語 #普通話 #vocabulary

Tips rambut cantik dari bahan alami. Say no to SLS, Paraben, Silikon. . Tahukah Anda kalau yogurt efektif untuk perawatan rambut? Produk olahan susu ini mengandung protein, zinc, dan lactic acid. Protein penting untuk menjaga kesehatan batang rambut. Sementara zinc dan lactic acid melancarkan peredaran darah ke kulit kepala. Sudah diketahui kalau sirkulasi darah yang lancar dapat membantu merangsang pertumbuhan rambut. . Selain itu, minyak alami dalam yogurt bisa menjadikan rambut lebih lembut, sehat, dan berkilau. . Untuk mendapatkan manfaat dari yogurt, Anda bisa menjadikannya bahan untuk conditioner atau masker rambut. . *jgn lupa guna shampoo santan by myhomelab* Jom back to the nature. Sayangi diri anda. . “A dangerous adventure that almost took my life, turned into one that changed it.  Home to the world’s third highest peak - the Kanchenjunga - Goechala is perhaps the best trek anyone can go for amidst the huge mountains in India.  Against the warnings of the villagers, I went ahead with the trek despite it being the monsoon season. I started having difficulty breathing as I slipped into having altitude sickness as I made my way up.  I was half conscious by this point and almost fell off a ledge. Luckily my guide grabbed me just in time, and he dragged me to the next checkpoint where I continued hyperventilating while he tried to warm me up. I was already having flashbacks of my family by then.  Eventually through medication, hot liquids, and lots of blankets to warm me up, I was conscious enough to make my way down. What if I actually died? I realised I hadn’t done much in life, and I knew I had to change.  I had 3 more weeks in India, and my cousin who was with me offered the chance to make a difference. Together we took a trip to Rajasthan, where we lived amongst the people there, understood their struggles, and during our stay, we also came across a school a school in disrepair, with no filtered water or even toilets.  That was how our social enterprise The Project Nomad @theprojnomad came to be. Skipping my internship and having that incident in the mountains definitely changed my entire perspective on life, and it is something I wouldn’t trade for anything else.” -Nasrul  #millennialsofsingapore  #millennials #singapore #yoursingapore #igsg #sgig #instasg #qotd #youth #singaporean #millennialsofsg

Initially wanted to pick up only the L'ORÉAL KERATIN SMOOTH 72H FRIZZ ERASER but Watsons had the 3 for 33% off previously. Took the chance to grab some never tried items like the Theramed 2in1 toothpaste & mouthrinse plus the Nivea Watering Lavendar lip balm.  Thoughts:  The L'oréal Keratin Smooth 72H Frizz Eraser does not only tame frizzes, it is also actually a heat protectant. It really aids the hair to not be puffy & stay in place. I am already on my second bottle because it WORKS SO WELL on my stubborn hair. The only thing that i don't like is the way the product dispers out at when sprayed from the bottle.  The Theramed is a nifty attempt to combine toothpaste & mouthrinse in 1 product. Works as intended but the packaging tends to make usage a little messy.  Lastly the Nivea Watering Lavender Lip Balm. Pretty generic, nothing to complain about. Walking around Singapore we came a cross a kid and his dad spinning flaming steel wool for a photography project (photographers will get it, non photogs may not but you just need to know this is the result ;) ). It's tough to miss; it's basically a ring of fire, this time at night in Singapore along the river. So I chatted him up and took some photos.  None of us were actually from Singapore. One topic we discussed was the legality of spinning fire in circles here. You don't want to break the law in Singapore!  Eventually we moved from out in the open along the river to this spot under a bridge.  Anyway I got some shots that he (the fire spinner) liked and I told him I'd email him when I got back to NY around mid April. I guess he got nervous and posted on Reddit after a few days passed looking for me.  https://www.reddit.com/r/newyork/comments/62ndgi/looking_for_a_new_york_photographer_who_was_near/dfojul4/?context=3 << turns out this post is about me.. Shoutout to my college buddy Alex Black for making the connection (and asking 'What color hair does he have?' ... Haa, sempena hari yang baik ini, jom baca kami nak SHARE 10 sebab kenapa kenapa kenapaa uolls WAJIB pilih Fairy Tears Potion (FTP) berbanding serum lain 😍🌸 . ⭐ BAU FTP berbau harum dengan ekstrak dewberry yang wangi & tidak terlalu kuat . ⭐ PENCERAH FTP mampu membuatkan kulit uolls kelihatan lebih putih merah jambu dan sangat mulus . ⭐ PARUT FTP sangat berkesan untuk mengatasi masalah parut yang tegar . ⭐ TAMPIL MUDA FTP bertindak menegangkan kulit yang kendur supaya lebih anjal, memudarkan garis halus & muda berseri . ⭐ MENYERAP JAUH FTP mampu meresap ke dalam lapisan terdalam kulit! Molekul dari formula zat umpama "lapisan vitamin" yang hebat . ⭐ TIDAK MELEKIT FTP cepat meresap ke kulit serta merta & tidak melekit . ⭐ MENYERAP MINYAK FTP terbaik untuk kulit berminyak / kulit kombinasi kerana ia dapat menyerap minyak berlebihan terutama di kawasan T-zone . ⭐ MELEMBABKAN FTP juga bagus dan sesuai untuk kulit kering kerana ianya mampu melembapkan & melembutkan . ⭐ MAKEUP TAHAN LAMA FTP memberi perlindungan untuk makeup bertahan lebih lama malah berseri-seri & kekal cantik sepanjang hari . ⭐ MENGECILKAN PORI-PORI FTP bertindak mengecilkan liang roma terbuka & besar yang menyebabkan jerawat, jeragat & bintik hitam . WOW. Nampak? Itu baru 10 SEBAB. Kalau uolls nak lebih pun weolls boleh kasi ok? 😂😘 . 新加坡不大，但要在兩天內遇到同一個人的機率應該也是很小的。  前天在中峇魯 (Tiong Bahru) 拍照，住在附近的這位婆婆以為我們是房仲業者，要來這邊拍房屋的照片，跟她解釋了一下我們真正的來意，在她離去後便繼續進行我們的漫步亂拍。  結果沒想到昨天在牛車水 (Chinatown) 附近的飲食中心又遇到她！她一認出是我們，便一直問我吃了沒，跟她說已經用餐了她還很熱情說「還可以吃，還可以吃」帶我們去吃 Oyster Cake（福州小吃，類似台灣的蚵嗲），不讓我結帳還一直要請我們「喝水」（這邊飲料都叫「水」），坐著跟我們聊到差點忘了時間。  人人都說新加坡店員通常臉臭，但我們倒覺得這邊的路人與居民通常都非常友善。我們要跟這位婆婆合照她也很乾脆的答應了，回去要把照片洗了寄給她，讓她也可以紀念這段很難得的緣份。  #MyBigBreak #Singapore

‌ از معروفترین #پل های جهان‌  این پل که بر روی رودخانه #سنگاپور قرار دارد، بواسطه طراحی خاصش که شبیه دی ان ای (DNA) می باشد، در لیست ما قرار می گیرد. ‌  پل مارپیچ در سال ۲۰۱۰ افتتاح شد و بیشتر سازه آن از فولاد تشکیل شده است. این پل زیبا که ۲۸۰ متر طول دارد و مارینای مرکزی را به مارینای جنوبی متصل می کند، در واقع شبیه مارپیچی است که گویی دو انتهای آن  در خلاف یکدیگر می چرخند. طرح بی‌نظیر سبب شد تا میلیون‌ها دلار در هزینه‌های ساخت‌و‌ساز صرفه‌جویی شود. ساخت این پل که نزدیک به سه سال طول کشید در نهایت با هزینه ۶۸ میلیون دلار به پایان رسید .درخشش چشم نواز پل در شب که بواسطه نور (LED) هاست، به خوبی بیانگر معماری منحصر بفرد آن می باشد. #singapore #helixbridge

LEBIH BANYAK MENDENGAR  Diantara fitnah orang yang berilmu (orang alim) ialah berkata-kata lebih disukai daripada mendengar. Padahal mendengar itu lebih selamat daripada berkata-kata karena dalam berkata-kata orang cenderung untuk mengisi, menambah dan mengurangi. (Yazid bin Abi Habib)  Penjelasan : Setiap manusia tentu saja ingin mengubah sesuatu dalam hidupnya menjadi lebih baik. Berbicara memang tak pernah salah, tetapi terkadang kata-kata atau kalimat yang muncul dari mulut kita justru menjadi bumerang bagi diri sendiri. Mendengarkan orang lain mungkin akan lebih baik, kita bisa mengambil sisi positif dari kalimat yang diucapkan orang lain.  Yang mesti kita ingat adalah tidak ada manusia yang dapat menjadi ahli dalam berbagai hal, meskipun menurut orang lain kita cerdas, meskipun menurut orang lain kita bijaksana, maka akan menjadi lebih cerdas dan bijaksana jika kita mampu mengelola kemampuan kita menjadi lebih optimal dengan tanpa banyak mengeluarkan banyak kalimat.  Rahasia kehebatan orang-orang besar bukan terletak pada banyaknya dia berbicara di depan umum, tetapi pada banyaknya tindakan dalam membuktikan hal-hal yang ia dengarkan dari orang-orang kecil yang justru bukan siapa-siapa, yang tak punya pangkat dan kedudukan. Singapore City Gallery is run by the Urban Redevelopment Authority and offers a fascinating look at how the country has developed over the past 200 years. Highlights include a huge scale model of the city centre, many interactive exhibitions and a preview of plans for the future, as well as the lengths gone to preserve cultural heritage, restore and protect the environment, and ensure the highest possible quality of  life for its some 5.4m residents. 2017. 3.9 - 7.2 #기획전 #상상적_아시아 - #싱가폴 #참여작가 #호_추_니엔 #작품 #소개 #Singapore #Artist #Ho_Tzu_Nyen #Artwork #Introduction - <미지의 구름(The Cloud of Unknowing)>, 2011, 단일채널 HD 비디오, 스테레오 음향, 17’00” < 미지의 구름> 은  신앙에 관한 14세기의 논문을 따라 붙인 제목으로, 여기서 구름은 미지의 혹은 신성한 경험에 대한 장애물인 동시에 화해를 의미하는 역설적 메타포이다. 싱가포르의 황량한 저소득층 주거단지에서 촬영한 이 작품은 8명의 등장인물과 이들 거주하는 아파트를 다룬다. 각각의 인물들은 틴토레토, 카라바치오, 르네 마그리트 등의 서양화가와 미불, 원청밍과 같은 동양화가의 작품 속에 등장하는 인물들을 상징 한다. 이 8명은 기이한 인물과 증기의 형태를 한 구름과 대면한다. 각기 다른 정체성을 가진 자아들이 하나의 동일한 인물과 동일한 상황을 조우할 때, 그 순간 각자 다른 감각의 이행, 전환, 조명이 발생한다.  호 추 니엔은 동서양의 문화, 역사, 철학 참고문헌을 혼합한 작품들을 선보이며 동남아시아, 특히 다민족으로 구성된 싱가폴인의 관점에서 현대 예술 담론을 표현하고 해석하는 어려움을 토로해왔다. <미지의 구름>은 이러한 통합을 통해 문화적 서사를 획기적으로 재해석하는 한편 동서양의 경계를 붕괴시킨다. - #NamJunePaikArtCenter #NamJunePaik #Imaginary_Asia #백남준아트센터 #백남준아트센터

When you met a half lion, this's what you do to chit chat with a lion! 😎 遇到半隻獅子時，就是要做獅子式跟他聊聊呀！  Merlion and Rosalion... Lol 魚尾獅和羅莎獅… 哈  Please advise how to be not so ugly when you practice simhasana... 😂  拜託告訴我要怎麼練習獅子式，臉才不會這麼醜…  I was reminding myself to move "tailbone in", but I forget about my lovely funny double chin. 我一直不斷的提醒自己尾骨收進去，但是卻忘了我可愛的雙下巴。  This happens a lot when you practice yogasana, you try to manage one part of body, but lost another part. (the double chin is just a joke though... Many parts of my body is not aligned.) I should practice simhasana more often. 這種顧此失彼的事常在體位法練習的時候發生呀…（當然雙下巴是開玩笑的… 我忘記了很多其他地方）我想我應該開始多練獅子式。  This's why continously practice is so important. 這也就是為什麼持續練習這麼重要！  #merlion #singapore #simhasana #yoga #yogafun #yogarosa108 #onedayinsingapore #merlionpark #lionpose #魚尾獅 #新加坡 #獅子式 #瑜珈

Due to the expanded codeshare agreement between Ethiopian airlines and Singapore airline. Under this agreement, Ethiopian Airlines customers will be able to access multiple destinations in Australia, China, Japan, Malaysia, New Zealand, Thailand and Vietnam across Singapore Airlines’ wide network. As well as  Singapore Airlines customers will enjoy access to Ethiopian Airlines’ vast intra-African network including countries like Botswana, Burkina Faso, Chad, Cote D’Ivoire, Kenya, Nigeria, Mozambique, The Republic of Congo, Rwanda, Seychelles, South Africa, Tanzania and Zimbabwe.  Mr. Girma Shiferaw, Acting Vice President, Strategic Planning and Alliances, remarked: “I wish to thank Singapore Airlines for the successful completion of this vital agreement..” also the Singapore Airlines Senior Vice President Marketing Planning, Mr Tan Kai Ping, said, "We are delighted with the expanded codeshare operations with Ethiopian Airlines. This significant expansion of our important partnership is in line with our ongoing effort to continuously expand our network reach and to offer customers more travel options and convenience when travelling between Africa, Asia and Southwest Pacific.” The two airlines will synergize their respective networks in Asia and Africa to offer customers the best connectivity options with one ticket and one single check-in at the first boarding airport. It will also play a critical role in enhancing investment, trade and tourism ties between a rising Africa, and a highly developed, innovative, and business-friendly Singapore. #travel #ethiopia #singapore #asia #africa #Tourism #networkmarketing #business #ambeels_world

Almeno in parte, tralasciando i dettagli inaspettati e le coincidenze 😏, avevamo previsto un disastro del genere 😂..ma di quelli positivi eh😏.. partendo in ritardo per la sveglia impostata male (avendo dormito solo 4 ore) vivendo un viaggio di andata di 5 ore di risate assurde 😅, proseguendo con lo scambiarsi le camere, (senza sapere ancora adesso il perché) con l'incontro assurdo del nostro amico 'Francesco Arca' 😱..(mini infarto gratuito)passando per il centro sconosciuto (solo per pochi minuti) di Mi.Ma, tra chi ci riconosceva e chi ci salutava urlando in bicicletta 😂.. arrivando in spiaggia dove abbiamo dato subito prova del nostro modo di essere sgarruppate,(anche scappando in mezzo alla gente coraggiosa, che prendeva il sole e faceva il bagno con 12 gradi 🤔).. e camminando all'inifinito, quasi del tutto a caso, per raggiungere la nostra meta.. (che per quei cattivi seguaci che non se ne fossero accorti, era il Papeete)😎 dalla quale non solo ci siamo fatte riconoscere in tempo record, ma abbiamo dato il via a una situazione infinita, di assoluto e fantastico degenero, che difficilmente dimenticheremo 😏🔝.. soprattutto per i follower e le loro dirette/le foto dai tetti/gli adesivi sulla pancia/le foto/ancora foto/i continui innamoramenti lampo/le corse a caso tra le sdraio/trovarsi a saltare sotto i gazebi/gli incontri del tutto casuali 😂/lo sputtanamento totale nelle ig stories/i bicchieri che cambiavano colore/le tante, tantissime figure di merda divertenti/le troppe risate e gli abbracci vari con tutti/il sorriso perenne/altre foto senza senso/i braccialettiiii 😍/ il freddo porco/il buio all'improvviso (ancora non capisco come abbia fatto a passare così velocemente dal giorno alla notte.. ed infine perderci senza sapere come, quando e perché 🙈.. ma dopo tutta questa recensione generale possiamo confermare di aver dato a quel posto e a quella gente il meglio e il peggio 😂..di noi stesse😇. Ps. I love you girls ❤

Saya pernah berbincang dengan rekan, juga dokter keluarga, artinya kalau diantara keluarga kami sedang mengalami gangguan kesehatan, kami akan berkonsultasi dengannya. Suatu ketika dia bilang; makan itu jangan hanya enak dimulut saja, tapi, buat perut akan menjadi masalah. Artinya, makanan yang enak itu, gurih, lezat, misal yang pakai bumbu penyedap MSG, atau santan kelapa misal pada soto dan ketupat sayur. Yang pertama ini saya paling suka, soto kaki, daging atau campur dengan iso atau usus sapi, atau jarit, paru atau daging yang masih bercampur lemak. Lantas, beberapa hari lalu saya berkunjung ke bywalk, Muara karang. Sebuah mall dengan pemandangan laut. Sungguh menggoda saat saya pesan sop buntut dengan buntut sapi yang di grill alias dipanggang. Fresh, dengan aroma bumbu kecap, bawang putih, lada. Belum sop bening yang dipisah dengan irisan wortel, kentang, daun seledri, aroma biji pala dan kayumanis. Berapa lama digodoknya untuk sop? Enam jam pak, sahut pelayan resto itu. Oh. Saya teringat sop buntut resto yang ada di Hotel Borobudur, Jakarta. Makin lama di masak dengan api kecil makin lezat buntut api dengan mengeluarkan kaldu. Oh iya kolesterol masih aman, dengan meminum obat. Tapi,tetap terkendali memasukkan makanan kedalam perut. Starting on a new novel! 😃 The author, Dawn Farnham, lived in Singapore for many years and was a docent with the Asian Civilisations Museum. It was there that she apparently got inspired to write these stories.  What was envisioned as a trilogy has since become a series of four volumes called The Straits Quartet. The Red Thread is the first book in the series!  My distributor & dear friend Leslie knows I'm into historical fiction at the moment and he's been a great recommender of books. 1830s Singapore? 😏  Aargh, that man!  So when I finished Balli Kaur Jaswal's book, Leslie's recommendation piqued my interest enough for me to do the unethical thing: I let this book jump my queue.  I have no idea whether I'll like it ~ I have not read any of her books. But as long as I know Farnham was herself intrigued by Singapore's colourful past and did thorough research (it's a journalist thing), I'm game for her to unleash her creativity and imagination on this historical platform.  Coolies. Peranakan family. 18-year-old Scots girl. Love. Fate. Kenapa senyum sampai ketelinga tu? Ada yang sudah mencuba minum suplemen ini itu, vitamin ini itu, obat ini itu, sandal peninggi badan ini itu, namun hasilnya Tiada.Sekarang pertanyaannya, kenapa begitu??? >•Untuk menjawab itu semua kami akan beri sebuah sudut pandang yang jarang dipikirkan orang .Kebanyakan customer membeli produk dengan menggunakan emosi.Bukankah Allah swt menganjurkan kita menggunakan akal untuk berpikir? >•Kenapa cara-cara diatas GAGAL membuat tinggi badan Anda bertambah? Karena proses menambah tinggi badan adalah proses tulang dan otot yang didapat dengan latihan terus menerus, bukan proses oral dan perut yang didapat secara instant. Saat Sperma Bertemu Sel Telur  Awal percobaan pembuahan terjadi ketika Anda dan pasangan sedang menikmati hubungan seksual. Saat mencapai orgasme, penis pria mengeluarkan cairan mani yang kaya dengan sperma ke dalam vagina. Cairan ini melesat ke dalam rahim mencari jalan untuk bertemu dengan sel telur. Kontraksi lembut pada rahim membantu sperma hidup dalam saluran reproduksi mencapai sel telur. Sperma-sperma akan melakukan perjalanan sepanjang kurang lebih 18 cm dari leher rahim ke tuba falopi di mana sel telur biasanya berada. Sperma pertama yang bertemu dengan sel telur akan berusaha menembus cangkang sel agar terjadi pembuahan. Umumnya sperma-sperma ini dapat berenang dengan kecepatan 2,5 cm tiap 15 menit. Beberapa sperma dapat menghabiskan waktu setengah hari untuk mencapai tujuan. Sementara sperma tercepat biasanya mencapai sel telur dalam waktu 45 menit. Pembuahan harus terjadi dalam waktu 24 jam setelah sel telur dihasilkan. Setelah salah satu sperma berhasil menembus sel telur, sel tersebut berubah bentuk sehingga sperma lain tidak bisa menembus masuk. Saat itulah janin terbentuk. Namun jika sperma tidak juga menemukan sel telur untuk dibuahi, mereka dapat tetap bertahan dalam tuba falopi hingga 7 hari setelah hubungan seksual. Jika dalam 7 hari tersebut wanita mengalami ovulasi, maka pasangan tersebut akan mendapatkan keturunan.  #miom #kista #azoospermia #asi #kistsurvivor #miomsurvivor #bayi #holistik #bengkulu #medan #rahim #singapore #melaka #malaysia #thailand #pejuangasi #pejuangkanker #bumil #kiathamil #anakbunda #anakkeren #freekonsultasi #ektopik #bayipintar #herbalBEE #herbalholistik #pcos #bumilssehat #bajubayi

“I got into theatre by complete accident. When I was in secondary one, I wanted to join the choir, but my school had this policy where students had to audition for every performing arts group that’s made available to them. Somehow, I ended up in Chinese Drama  Back then, my Chinese was terrible. During the audition, they made me read this really difficult passage with a lot of words I didn’t even know. They also asked questions like why I was there and why I wanted to join the club.  For every Chinese word I spoke, I spoke about 10 English words; it was the worst audition ever. When I got in, I had to use a classroom ruler to match my name to the assigned club, just to make sure they had me in the right place  I’m effectively bilingual now partly because of my training in Chinese drama, but I think my Chinese was horrible because I read a lot of English books growing up. My parents also spoke primarily in English, so I had a hard time communicating with my grandma as a kid.  Apparently, I rolled around the floor and pretended to be a ball because I didn’t know how to convey that I wanted an orange. It took her half an hour to figure out what I wanted. I even told my mom one time that I wasn’t Chinese, and she was absolutely horrified!  My first memory of learning Chinese? I was five. I was actually bullied in kindergarten because I wasn’t like the other kids. Everyone was very Chinese-speaking and it gave me social anxiety. The trauma made me associate Chinese with ‘bad people’ and English with my safe environment.  Now that I’m older, I think it’s very important to have a grasp of both English and your Mother Tongue. Beyond the cultural significance, it’s what helps you communicate with people. My Cantonese, for instance, is very subpar, but I can at least understand what my grandparents are saying.  I’m even learning French and Malay. My father is Malaysian, and learning the language helps bridge my Malaysian relatives and I. Sometimes they would crack jokes and I would go ‘Uh huh! I get it!’. It’s really cool when you don’t need someone to translate something for you, and you feel like you can get to know somebody better.” - Esther, 23

Truffle Gyumeshi $16.9 - Deceivingly visually appealing, but what a letdown. Dry and hard rice that tastes like it's been in the fridge for too long, slightly tough beef, and dried truffle slices devoid of any fragrance or flavour except for a barely there nuttiness. I really needed the honey truffle soy to moisten things up a little, but there was barely any of it, and what I was left with was the bad synthetic aftertaste of really cheap tasting truffle oil. - Service was slightly bumbling, and the food was on par with previous experiences at other branches, which is to say, not good. The only redeeming factor is pints of Archipelago go for $9++ during happy hour. - Platypus Kitchen Santa Grand Hotel East Coast

Terus di sistem jaringan adanya pembinaan, jadi Sponsor atau Upline harus membina mitra-mitranya, jadi jangan iri kalau ada mitra bilang, wuih enak saya kerja dia yang dapat hasil. Nah kalau kita tidak diperkenalkan PayTren dan tidak dibina oleh Upline atau Sponsor apakah bisa sukses juga. 🔸 Jadi secara syariah ini sudah Syar’i adil dari pembagian hasilnya. Dan dengan Konsep jaringan ini bisa membentuk komunitas yang bisa mempererat persaudaraan ataupun bisa saling bantu sesama mitra terutama dari Upline kepada Mitra dibawahnya. 🔸 DSN MUI sudah mengeluarkan fatwa tentang MLM dengan nama Penjualan Langsung Berjenjang Syariah No 75 Tahun 2009. 🔸 👌 . Before we even talk about the taste, lets touch on the horrible service of this place. Customers were allowed in in batches of six causing this never ending queue snaking outside the place. When we asked why, apparently it was because their "machine" can only do six bowls at one time. So after every six bowls, six more people get to enter and the staff takes a ten minute break standing around doing nothing while the "machine" works. We asked why do they even try to cater to such a big crowd if their one and only "only-6-bowls-at-one-time-machine" and the response was "because the machine at first can do 12 but the quality not good so we cut down to 6". Us:"so why aren't u even upgrading the machine to cater to the crowd? Does it reflect very well?" Them:"But u must understand, the machine only can do 6. We can do many, but it won't be as nice. Because our kitchen is small". Responses didn't make sense and all they could blame was the poor "6-bowl-maker machine" (Poor machine お疲れ様です). Oh and the taste? Forgettable. Just go to Itsuki.

Michael's House. . With its unique mix of ten bungalow homes and thirty semi-detached units, Michael’s Residences is a premium development set in the heart of the lush natural greenery that extends from the nearby Dairy Farm Nature Park. Wholly designed and developed by ONG&ONG, this splendidly luxuriant residence is the result of a successful collaboration achieving a collective goal, which was to offer the sophisticating consumer public a fresh residential concept. . Minimal bounding and demarcation allows the individual gardens fluidity, converging to form a lush communal green space, connecting the entire development. Balancing the boldness of the communal garden are subtle features that delineate spaces within the Michael’s grounds. From boundary cues in the form of postboxes and concealed security gates, to understated shifts in material that distinguish different areas within the development. . The Michaels’ development also considers aspects of sustainable, tropical living – a philosophy that ONG&ONG champions. Cross-ventilation design principles are embodied into the spatial layout, with generous overhangs and moveable screens introduced to shield homes the elements.

【普通人午餐】 曾经有个朋友在上班时间来找我聊一些事情，午餐时间都忙不可开交，我买了鸡饭给他一起在办公室吃饭盒。他问我一句：以为你每餐都出去找好吃。。。。。。。呵呵！通常只有周末有时间才可以出外觅食，或者有朋友相约，不然平日都是如此吃饭盒或回去娘家吃午餐啊！  现在在新加坡没有回去娘家吃午餐，自己简单弄一餐。普通人午餐就是三餐温饱，我也不忘要营养均衡，顺便瘦身！呵呵！  题外话：李宗盛的理性与感性作品音乐会是我经常听的，已经听了几个月，我都不厌倦。 《鬼迷心窍》是我最喜欢听，喜欢他和周华健合唱默契 《领悟》没有辛晓琪的痛，但是感受到痛后大悟。 《我终于失去了你》的开场幽默，我也喜欢！  怎么当年我错过了这场音乐会，日后我期待他开演唱会！  #bento #lunch #sonnyangel #totoro #singapore #food #instafood
